<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
One curious record of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. indica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rathbun, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Lingnan Science Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="75 - 125" refId="B61" refString="Rathbun, MJ, 1931. New and rare Chinese crabs. Lingnan Science Journal 8: 75 - 125" title="New and rare Chinese crabs." volume="8" year="1931">Rathbun (1931)</bibRefCitation>
from Tsimei, Amoy (= Jimei, Xiamen), along the coasts of Fujian. Other than this record, there have been no definite records of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. indica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from China, despite that of 
<bibRefCitation author="Shen, CJ" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Fan Memorial Institute of Biology (Zoology)" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="69 - 104" refId="B68" refString="Shen, CJ, 1940a. On the collections of crabs of South China. Bulletin of the Fan Memorial Institute of Biology (Zoology) 10: 69 - 104" title="On the collections of crabs of South China." volume="10" year="1940 a">Shen (1940a)</bibRefCitation>
citing that of 
<bibRefCitation author="Rathbun, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Lingnan Science Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="75 - 125" refId="B61" refString="Rathbun, MJ, 1931. New and rare Chinese crabs. Lingnan Science Journal 8: 75 - 125" title="New and rare Chinese crabs." volume="8" year="1931">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Rathbun’s">Rathbun's</normalizedToken>
(1931)
</bibRefCitation>
. Given the considerable resemblance between 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. indica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3048.1.1" author="Naderloo, R" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 43" refId="B51" refString="Naderloo, R, 2011. Grapsoid crabs (Decapoda: Brachyura: Thoracotremata) of the Persian Gulf and the Gulf of Oman. Zootaxa 3048: 1 - 43" title="Grapsoid crabs (Decapoda: Brachyura: Thoracotremata) of the Persian Gulf and the Gulf of Oman." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3048.1.1" volume="3048" year="2011">Naderloo 2011</bibRefCitation>
: figs 15, 18
<normalizedToken originalValue="c–d">c-d</normalizedToken>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-49374-9" author="Naderloo, R" journalOrPublisher="Springer, Cham, Switzerland" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B52" refString="Naderloo, R, 2017. Atlas of crabs of the Persian Gulf. Springer, Cham, Switzerland" title="Atlas of crabs of the Persian Gulf." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-49374-9" year="2017">Naderloo 2017</bibRefCitation>
: figs 31.11e, 32.2, 32.3) and 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. sheni" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="sheni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. sheni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the latter described from the region (Amoy) shortly before, it is reasonable to consider 
<bibRefCitation author="Rathbun, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Lingnan Science Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="75 - 125" refId="B61" refString="Rathbun, MJ, 1931. New and rare Chinese crabs. Lingnan Science Journal 8: 75 - 125" title="New and rare Chinese crabs." volume="8" year="1931">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Rathbun’s">Rathbun's</normalizedToken>
(1931)
</bibRefCitation>
record represented 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. sheni" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="sheni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. sheni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Specimens collected from Kinmen, opposite Xiamen (Fujian, China), are confirmed as 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. sheni" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="sheni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. sheni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on molecular analyses (see below), being a new record to Taiwan.
</paragraph>
